  "distance": "308.405 km (191.634 miles)",
  "event_preview": "Circuit of the Americas measures 5.513 km (3.426 mi) and features 20 turns in Austin, Texas — the first purpose-built Formula 1 facility in the United States, opened in 2012. Designed by Hermann Tilke in collaboration with Kevin Schwantz, the layout is a deliberate greatest-hits compilation of legendary circuit elements: a spectacular 41-metre climb into the wide, sweeping Turn 1, a high-speed Silverstone-inspired Maggotts-Becketts sequence through Turns 3–6, Suzuka-style esses and a Hockenheim stadium section to close the lap. Running counterclockwise, COTA places unusual physical demands on drivers and splits tyre loading evenly between axles, while the fierce Texan heat — even in October — keeps thermal degradation at the forefront of every strategy call. A partial resurfacing in 2024 improved smoothness without stripping the track of its character. The official race lap record stands at 1:36.139, set by Charles Leclerc for Ferrari during the 2019 United States Grand Prix, while the all-time qualifying lap record belongs to Valtteri Bottas, who clocked a 1:32.029 for Mercedes in Q3 of that same weekend.",
